                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1025: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-17T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 17, 1930—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. Your 105, December 16, 8 p.m. Please report at once what American interests
                    may be affected by the present situation in Guatemala and consequently require
                    protection.</p>
                <p>Has Mr. Edwin C. Wilson arrived?<note n="1" xml:id="d132fn1">Foreign Service
                        Inspector.</note> If so, transmit his opinion with regard to the
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
